# Pinterest Clone Project

## Introduction

Welcome to the Pinterest clone project! This web application allows users to discover and save images to personalized boards. Users can create, edit, and delete boards, pin images to them, and explore pins created by other users. The project also features user authentication and authorization to ensure a secure and personalized experience.

## Prerequisites

Before you dive into the project, make sure you have the following installed on your system:

- Node.js
- npm
- MongoDB

## Getting Started

### Installation

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/pinterest-clone.git

# Change directory
cd pinterest-clone

# Install dependencies
npm install
Configuration
Create a .env file in the root directory and provide the necessary environment variables:

env
Copy code
PORT=3000
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/pinterest_clone
SESSION_SECRET=your_session_secret
Run the Application
bash
Copy code
# Start the application
npm start
Visit http://localhost:3000 in your browser to access the Pinterest clone.
